  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "22 \u0b86\u0bb5\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bae\u0bcd \u0bae\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0b8f\u0bae\u0bbe\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b95\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b95\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbf \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc8 - \u0bb2\u0b95\u0bcd\u0bb7\u0bcd\u0bae\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bc6\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "22nd Amendment is a gimmick to deceive people - Laxman Kiriella",
      "author": "Vishnu",
      "body_lines": [
        "22nd amendment is a gimmick to fool people. By this the power of the President has been increased.",
        "Similarly, Opposition Chief Whip Laxman Kiriella said that there is no use in setting up departmental oversight committees without bringing back the 19th Amendment.",
        "During the Prime Minister's special speech in the Parliament on 06th Wednesday, he mentioned this in response to the statement that he had taken steps to set up departmental oversight committees and give their chairmanship to the opposition party.",
        "A Parliamentary Sectoral Oversight Committee is essential. However, without bringing back the 19th Amendment, there is no point in setting up departmental oversight committees.",
        "Similarly, the Prime Minister had said that government institutions should be rescued from government interference.",
        "We did the same with the 19th Amendment. But bringing in the 20th amendment has completely abolished it.",
        "Because the institutions have brought everything under the President. So how can government institutions be protected from political interference? Therefore, as stated by the Prime Minister, it is not possible to form a committee and protect government institutions.",
        "Also, the committee system to be formed by the Prime Minister is not in the constitution. These groups are organized by us on a friendly basis. It has no authority. Even if we discuss and take a decision, the President may not implement it. So bring the 19 that you brought initially.",
        "And the 22nd amendment brought by Minister Wijetasa Rajapaksh is not the 19th amendment. Initially, the Prime Minister had shown everyone the same amendment bill as the 19th Amendment.",
        "But later it was amended and the 22nd Amendment increased the powers of the President.",
        "You as the Prime Minister can be removed at any time. This is also a brilliant trick. So if you are going to bring the committee system, bring the Donamoore system into the constitution.",
        "We support it. He said that if the Donamoor system is brought to the constitution and these committees are formed, it can function properly."
      ],
